<br>
1) Are you saying that my aggro count goes up when I get buffed? Does this happen only when the buffer/I am in range of the mob or are you saying EQ keeps a record of buffing so it can get from the FD'd monk to the buffer to me? I rarely get buffed mid battle. I can't remember ever getting aggro due to getting a buff.<br>
<br>
2) I guess I don't understand rampage at all. As a wizard, I see the rampage messages, but really have no I idea what they mean. It sounds like mobs rampage against a single pc. Correct? What happens? Just lots of hits? Do people agree that mobs keep a rampage list ordered by when people do first damage (subject to memblur)? Gusty said that the PC top of the hate list will never get rampaged, does this mean the mob will move to the next PC on the rampage list? Is a rampage tank someone who's job is to be the one who is 2nd to hit the mob after the MT? What determines how long a rampage lasts? If a tank and I are the only PCs to hit a rampaging mob, assuming tanks gets aggro, does this mean that the mob will always rampage me?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
Tyrillian<br>
