<br>
If the buffer does NOT have agro, he can buff you for days on end and nobody will get agro. <br>
<br>
There are a number of ways a buffer can get agro, but sorry to say, I'm not going to attempt to list them all<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I will say however, that it's possible the monk in the situation above FD'd, and got a heal or something, the mob chased him back to the group, and when he FD'ed again to clear agro, the mob went for the 1st agro target he saw, which was a wizard that probably got buffed ot healed by the guy that healed the monk.  <p><b>Sage Flintnilf Ironori</b>

